# UI Optimization Guidelines

## Performance Considerations
- Use `const` constructors for widgets that don't change
- Implement `RepaintBoundary` for complex animations or frequently updating widgets
- Avoid rebuilding large widget trees by using selective state updates
- Use `ListView.builder` instead of `ListView` for long lists
- Implement pagination for data-heavy screens

## Animation Guidelines
- Keep animations under 300ms for UI feedback
- Use implicit animations when possible (AnimatedContainer, AnimatedOpacity)
- For complex animations, use explicit animation controllers
- Ensure animations run at 60fps by avoiding expensive operations during animation

## Asset Loading
- Preload assets that will be needed immediately
- Load other assets asynchronously
- Consider using caching for frequently accessed assets
- Implement loading indicators for content that takes time to load

## Responsive Design
- Use `MediaQuery` to adapt layouts to different screen sizes
- Implement flexible layouts using Expanded, Flexible, and FractionallySizedBox
- Test layouts on multiple device sizes
- Use LayoutBuilder for more complex responsive behaviors

## Game Board Optimization
- Use efficient data structures for the game board
- Implement custom painters for specialized rendering needs
- Consider using a grid-based approach for the game board
- Optimize touch detection algorithms for game piece selection